                        <p class="Para">Most of the biggest financial or insurance companies in the world that deal with critical client information are now considering introducing a Data Leakage Protection(DLP) system in order to reduce the risk of data loss. However, there is no standard for the introduction of a DLP system, which leads to companies still having the problem of information leakage even after the introduction. This paper analyzes various channels of information leakage and suggests a protection profile based on the CC V3.1 to help develop and introduce a DLP system that can prevent in-house information leakage.</p>
